---

<BaseLayout
  title="APIOps Paris 2026 - After API Management"
  description="APIOps Paris 2026 is the APIOps Operating Model Day for senior practitioners turning API platform investment into enterprise adoption, AI-speed, and governed digital capabilities."
>
  <nav class="paris-nav">
    <div class="container nav-inner">
      <a class="brand" href="/">
        <img class="brand-logo" src="/favicon-32x32.png" alt="APIOps Paris logo" />
        <strong>APIOps Paris</strong>
      </a>

      <button
        class="nav-toggle"
        type="button"
        aria-label="Toggle navigation menu"
        aria-expanded="false"
        aria-controls="top-navigation"
      >
        <span></span>
        <span></span>
        <span></span>
      </button>

      <div class="nav-links" id="top-navigation">
        <a href="#why">Why</a>
        <a href="#program">Program</a>
        <a href="#stations">Stations</a>
        <a href="#cycles">APIOps Cycles</a>
        <a href="#updates">Get Program Updates</a>
        <a class="button primary" href={ticketUrl}>Get Early Bird Ticket</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </nav>

  <script>
    const navToggle = document.querySelector(".nav-toggle");
    const navLinks = document.querySelector(".nav-links");

    navToggle?.addEventListener("click", () => {
      navLinks?.classList.toggle("is-open");
      const isExpanded = navLinks?.classList.contains("is-open") || false;
      navToggle.setAttribute("aria-expanded", String(isExpanded));
    });

    window.addEventListener("resize", () => {
      if (window.innerWidth > 720 && navLinks?.classList.contains("is-open")) {
        navLinks.classList.remove("is-open");
        navToggle?.setAttribute("aria-expanded", "false");
      }
    });
  </script>

  <main class="paris-page">
    <header class="paris-hero">
      <div class="container paris-hero-grid">
        <div class="paris-hero-copy">
          <p class="paris-eyebrow">December 1, 2026 - FOST Paris</p>
          <h1>APIOps Paris 2026</h1>
          <p class="paris-hero-subtitle">After API Management</p>
          <p class="paris-hero-day">The APIOps Operating Model Day</p>
          <p class="paris-hero-lede">
            From API platform investment to enterprise adoption, AI-speed, and governed digital capabilities.
          </p>
          <p>
            API management platforms, gateways, portals, standards, and governance models are only the
            beginning.
          </p>
          <p>
            The hard part starts after the platform decision: getting product teams to adopt the paved road,
            making APIs visible and reusable, engaging security and compliance early, reducing shadow APIs,
            supporting AI-speed, managing B2B developer change, and proving business value before the full
            enterprise capability is ready.
          </p>
          <div class="paris-actions">
            <a class="button primary" href={ticketUrl}>Get Early Bird Ticket</a>
            <a class="button secondary" href={contributorUrl}>Propose a Program Contribution</a>
          </div>
          <a class="paris-hero-link" href={challengeUrl}>Share an APIOps Challenge</a>
        </div>

        <div class="paris-visual" aria-label="Paris operating model map">
          <div class="paris-skyline" aria-hidden="true">
            <span class="tower"></span>
            <span class="block block-1"></span>
            <span class="block block-2"></span>
            <span class="block block-3"></span>
          </div>
          <div class="paris-map-card">
            <span>How do we get adoption?</span>
            <span>How do we explain APIs to executives?</span>
            <span>Where are our shadow APIs?</span>
            <span>Can AI help without creating chaos?</span>
            <span>How do we prove business value?</span>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </header>

    <section class="paris-proof-strip">
      <div class="container paris-proof-grid">
        <div>
          <strong>1 day</strong>
          <span>working conference</span>
        </div>
        <div>
          <strong>11</strong>
          <span>APIOps Cycles stations</span>
        </div>
        <div>
          <strong>90 days</strong>
          <span>proof-plan horizon</span>
        </div>
        <div>
          <strong>No pitches</strong>
          <span>practical patterns only</span>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="section section-light" id="why">
      <div class="container paris-two-column">
        <div class="paris-section-intro">
          <p class="small-pill">Why After API Management?</p>
          <h2>The hard part starts after the platform decision.</h2>
        </div>
        <div class="paris-copy-stack">
          <p>
            APIOps Paris is a full-day working conference for senior practitioners turning API platform
            investment into enterprise adoption, production use, governance, and reusable digital capabilities.
          </p>
          <p>
            Many organizations already have API management initiatives, cloud gateways, developer portals, API
            standards, platform roadmaps, or integration modernization programs. They still struggle with
            adoption, ownership, funding, governance, production usage, and executive understanding.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="section section-soft">
      <div class="container paris-outcomes-grid">
        <div>
          <p class="small-pill">What You Leave With</p>
          <h2>Practical outputs, not just notes from talks.</h2>
        </div>
        <div class="paris-outcome-list">
          {outcomes.map((outcome) => <p>{outcome}</p>)}
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="section section-light" id="credibility">
      <div class="container paris-two-column">
        <div class="paris-section-intro">
          <p class="small-pill">Built from practitioner conversations</p>
          <h2>This day comes from real APIOps clinics, not a generic call for talks.</h2>
        </div>
        <div class="paris-copy-stack">
          <p>
            APIOps Paris is shaped by recurring questions from APIOps clinics, workshops, and senior practitioner
            conversations. The same themes keep coming back: platform adoption after API management investment,
            shadow APIs, executive language, control-team involvement, AI-speed, B2B developer change, and how to
            prove progress before the full enterprise capability is ready.
          </p>
          <p>
            The agenda is built around these recurring operating-model questions, not sponsor tracks.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="section section-soft">
      <div class="container paris-audience-layout">
        <div>
          <p class="small-pill">Who Should Attend</p>
          <h2>Built for senior practitioners and decision-shapers.</h2>
          <p>
            This is especially relevant if your organization has already invested in API platforms or API
            strategy, but still struggles with adoption, ownership, funding, governance, production usage, or
            executive understanding.
          </p>
          <div class="paris-inline-actions">
            <a class="button primary" href={ticketUrl}>Get Early Bird Ticket</a>
            <a class="button secondary alt" href={challengeUrl}>Share an APIOps Challenge</a>
          </div>
        </div>
        <ul class="paris-audience-list">
          {audience.map((item) => <li>{item}</li>)}
        </ul>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="section agenda-showcase" id="program">
      <div class="container">
        <div class="section-title section-title-left section-title-compact">
          <h2>Program</h2>
          <p>One focused day from diagnosis to next decision.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="paris-agenda">
          {agenda.map((item) => (
            <article class="paris-agenda-row">
              <time>{item.time}</time>
              <div>
                <h3>{item.title}</h3>
                <p>{item.detail}</p>
              </div>
            </article>
          ))}
        </div>

        <div class="paris-section-actions">
          <a class="button primary" href={ticketUrl}>Get Early Bird Ticket</a>
          <a class="button secondary alt" href={contributorUrl}>Propose a Program Contribution</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="section paris-image-band">
      <div class="container paris-image-grid">
        <figure>
          <img src="/images/hero/apiops-helsinki2026-allan-knabe-jurgen-buchmann-preparing-clinic.jpg" alt="APIOps practitioners preparing a working clinic" loading="lazy" />
        </figure>
        <div>
          <p class="small-pill">How the day works</p>
          <h2>A participant-shaped working room.</h2>
          <p>
            The day combines short practitioner provocations, APIOps Cycles station stickers, guided station
            clinics, peer problem-solving, facilitated roundtables, live synthesis, and practical outputs.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="section section-light" id="stations">
      <div class="container">
        <div class="paris-stations-layout" data-station-system>
          <div class="paris-stations-copy">
            <p class="small-pill">Choose your APIOps stations</p>
            <h2>Your stickers help you find the right conversations.</h2>
            <div class="paris-stations-intro">
              <p>
                APIOps Cycles is an open method. At APIOps Paris, we use its stations as a shared navigation
                system for the day.
              </p>
              <p>
                At registration, you'll choose station stickers that match the challenges you want to work on.
              </p>
              <p>
                The stickers help you find relevant peers, join the right station clinics, and make the room's
                priorities visible.
              </p>
            </div>

            <ol class="paris-station-steps" aria-label="How APIOps station stickers work">
              {stationSteps.map((step) => <li>{step}</li>)}
            </ol>

            <div class="paris-badge-stack" aria-label="Example APIOps Paris badges with station stickers">
              {badgeExamples.map((badge, index) => (
                <article class={`paris-badge-mockup badge-angle-${index + 1}`}>
                  <div class="paris-badge-lanyard" aria-hidden="true"></div>
                  <header>
                    <span>APIOps Paris</span>
                    <small>Dec 1 / FOST Paris</small>
                  </header>
                  <strong>{badge.name}</strong>
                  <small>{badge.role}</small>
                  <div class="paris-badge-stickers">
                    {badge.stickers.map((stickerName) => {
                      const sticker = stickerByName.get(stickerName);
                      return (
                        <button
                          class={`station-mini-sticker station-${sticker?.color ?? "blue"}`}
                          type="button"
                          data-station-trigger={sticker?.id}
                          aria-label={`Highlight ${stickerName} station: ${sticker?.problem ?? "APIOps challenge"}`}
                        >
                          {stickerName}
                        </button>
                      );
                    })}
                  </div>
                </article>
              ))}
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="paris-stations-visual">
            <div class="apiops-map-card">
              <div class="apiops-map-label">APIOps Cycles open method</div>
              <div class="apiops-map-scroll">
                <div class="apiops-map-stage">
                  <img
                    src="/images/metro_map.svg"
                    alt="APIOps Cycles metro map showing stations used as the APIOps Paris navigation system"
                    loading="lazy"
                  />
                  <div class="apiops-map-pins" aria-hidden="true">
                    {stationStickers.map((station) => (
                      <span
                        class={`apiops-map-pin station-${station.color}`}
                        data-station-pin={station.id}
                        style={`left: ${station.position.left}%; top: ${station.position.top}%;`}
                      ></span>
                    ))}
                  </div>
                  <div class="apiops-floating-stickers">
                    {stationStickers
                      .filter((station) => station.featured)
                      .map((station) => (
                        <button
                          class={`station-sticker station-${station.color}`}
                          type="button"
                          data-station-trigger={station.id}
                          style={`--pin-left: ${station.position.left}%; --pin-top: ${station.position.top}%; --sticker-rotate: ${station.rotation}deg;`}
                          aria-label={`Highlight ${station.name} station: ${station.problem}`}
                        >
                          <span>{station.name}</span>
                          <small>{station.problem}</small>
                        </button>
                      ))}
                  </div>
                </div>
              </div>
              <p class="apiops-map-caption" data-station-caption>
                Pick a station to find peers working on the same challenge.
              </p>
            </div>

            <div class="station-sticker-strip" aria-label="Popular APIOps Cycles station stickers">
              {stationStickers.map((station) => (
                <button
                  class={`station-sticker station-${station.color}`}
                  type="button"
                  data-station-trigger={station.id}
                  aria-label={`Highlight ${station.name} station: ${station.problem}`}
                >
                  <span>{station.name}</span>
                  <small>{station.problem}</small>
                </button>
              ))}
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="paris-station-links">
          <a href="#cycles">Explore APIOps Cycles stations</a>
          <a href={challengeUrl}>Share an APIOps challenge</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <script define:vars={{ stations: stationStickers }}>
      const stationSystem = document.querySelector("[data-station-system]");

      if (stationSystem) {
        const triggers = Array.from(stationSystem.querySelectorAll("[data-station-trigger]"));
        const pins = Array.from(stationSystem.querySelectorAll("[data-station-pin]"));
        const caption = stationSystem.querySelector("[data-station-caption]");
        const stationMap = new Map(stations.map((station) => [station.id, station]));

        const setActiveStation = (stationId) => {
          const station = stationMap.get(stationId);

          triggers.forEach((trigger) => {
            trigger.classList.toggle("is-active", trigger.dataset.stationTrigger === stationId);
          });

          pins.forEach((pin) => {
            pin.classList.toggle("is-active", pin.dataset.stationPin === stationId);
          });

          if (caption && station) {
            caption.textContent = `${station.name} - ${station.problem}`;
          }
        };

        const clearActiveStation = () => {
          triggers.forEach((trigger) => trigger.classList.remove("is-active"));
          pins.forEach((pin) => pin.classList.remove("is-active"));

          if (caption) {
            caption.textContent = "Pick a station to find peers working on the same challenge.";
          }
        };

        triggers.forEach((trigger) => {
          trigger.addEventListener("mouseenter", () => setActiveStation(trigger.dataset.stationTrigger));
          trigger.addEventListener("focus", () => setActiveStation(trigger.dataset.stationTrigger));
          trigger.addEventListener("mouseleave", clearActiveStation);
          trigger.addEventListener("blur", clearActiveStation);
          trigger.addEventListener("click", () => setActiveStation(trigger.dataset.stationTrigger));
        });
      }
    </script>

    <section class="section section-soft" id="format">
      <div class="container">
        <div class="section-title section-title-left section-title-compact">
          <h2>Questions senior practitioners are asking</h2>
          <p>The day is built around recurring APIOps challenges from clinics, workshops, and enterprise conversations.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="paris-question-grid">
          <article>
            <h3>What happens after API platform investment?</h3>
            <p>Move from rollout to adoption, reuse, production usage, governance, and measurable value.</p>
          </article>
          <article>
            <h3>How do we talk to CXOs about API programs?</h3>
            <p>Find language that creates traction instead of making APIs sound like a technical side topic.</p>
          </article>
          <article>
            <h3>How do we support AI-speed without chaos?</h3>
            <p>Use AI in API design and delivery without multiplying inconsistency.</p>
          </article>
          <article>
            <h3>How do we manage B2B developer change?</h3>
            <p>Handle migration pressure, roadmap tension, ecosystem expectations, and partner trust.</p>
          </article>
          <article>
            <h3>Where are our shadow APIs and duplicated integrations?</h3>
            <p>Make hidden interfaces visible without launching a heavy governance program.</p>
          </article>
          <article>
            <h3>How do we involve control teams earlier?</h3>
            <p>Bring security, privacy, legal, risk, and compliance into the paved road before they become blockers.</p>
          </article>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="section section-light" id="cycles">
      <div class="container paris-two-column">
        <div class="paris-section-intro">
          <p class="small-pill">How APIOps Cycles is used</p>
          <h2>An open and optional method for navigating API program work.</h2>
        </div>
        <div class="paris-copy-stack">
          <p>
            APIOps Cycles is an open method for understanding, designing, and improving the digital capability
            operating model behind APIs and related capabilities.
          </p>
          <p>
            It is not a vendor product. It is not a mandatory framework. It is one practical way to make the
            APIOps conversation visible across business, governance, platform, design, delivery, publishing,
            adoption, and continuous improvement.
          </p>
          <p>
            At APIOps Paris, APIOps Cycles is used as a shared navigation tool. Participants choose station
            stickers to show where their organization is currently stuck, find relevant peers, join focused
            clinics, and connect local challenges to a broader enterprise API capability.
          </p>
          <p>
            The goal is not to follow a method. The goal is to help participants understand and improve the
            operating model for their own organization.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="section paris-contributors" id="contributors">
      <div class="container paris-contributor-grid">
        <div>
          <p class="small-pill">For program contributors and station hosts</p>
          <h2>Practical patterns do. Product demos do not.</h2>
          <p>
            APIOps Paris is shaped by selected program contributors: practitioners who bring real decision
            stories, facilitation, case examples, and reusable operating patterns.
          </p>
          <p>
            Some contributors work in enterprises. Some work in consultancies. Some work for vendors. That is
            fine. Their role in this program is not to sell. Their role is to help the room work through real
            APIOps questions.
          </p>
          <a class="button primary" href={contributorUrl}>Propose a Program Contribution</a>
        </div>
        <div class="paris-contributor-panel">
          <h3>Program contributors may take part as:</h3>
          <div class="paris-patterns">
            {contributorRoles.map((role) => <span>{role}</span>)}
          </div>
          <h3>A strong contribution helps participants answer:</h3>
          <ul>
            {contributionQuestions.map((question) => <li>{question}</li>)}
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="section section-light" id="support">
      <div class="container paris-two-column">
        <div class="paris-section-intro">
          <p class="small-pill">Support and collaboration</p>
          <h2>Collaborate with APIOps.</h2>
        </div>
        <div class="paris-copy-stack">
          <p>
            Official Paris event sponsorship is handled by the FOST/apidays team. We are happy to talk about
            possibilities to support and collaborate with the APIOps Community and the open APIOps Cycles method.
          </p>
          <div class="paris-inline-actions">
            <a class="button primary" href={partnershipUrl}>Contact about partnerships and collaboration</a>
            <a class="button secondary alt" href={contributorUrl}>Propose a Program Contribution</a>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="section section-soft" id="faq">
      <div class="container">
        <div class="community-section-head">
          <p class="small-pill">FAQ</p>
          <h2>Common questions about tickets, challenges, contributors, and collaboration.</h2>
        </div>
        <div class="paris-faq-grid">
          {faqs.map((faq) => (
            <article>
              <h3>{faq.question}</h3>
              <p>{faq.answer}</p>
            </article>
          ))}
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="section cta-band cta-section" id="tickets">
      <div class="container">
        <h2>Bring a real APIOps problem.</h2>
        <p>
          Leave with better language, practical patterns, and a sharper next decision for your own organization.
        </p>
        <div class="hero-actions cta-actions">
          <a class="button primary" href={ticketUrl}>Get Early Bird Ticket</a>
          <a class="button secondary" href={updatesUrl}>Get Program Updates</a>
        </div>
        <p class="paris-cta-note" id="updates">
          Not ready to buy a ticket yet? Get APIOps Paris updates as the program develops. This does not reserve
          a seat. Tickets are sold through FOST/apidays.
        </p>
        <a class="paris-cta-link" href={challengeUrl}>Share an APIOps Challenge</a>
      </div>
    </section>
  </main>

